Commands Used:

ls - list command
can pass additional directories to ls to list at one time:
ie.
	ls ~/ /usr/ ~/Desktop
this will list all of the items in those directories.. 

most useful options:
-a --lists all of the files including hidden ones..
-t --sort by time
-h --make human readable..
-l --long format to show edit time, and file size

file - used to determine a file's type..

less - optional text viewer compared to nano or more..

